# BOTMK3 Leakage & Causality Audit Report (Sprint 4)

This audit matrix explicitly documents all potential data leakage vectors and temporal assumptions within the BOTMK3 pipeline, tracing data from exchange payload ingestion to Orchestrator execution.

## Audit Matrix

| Vector | Description | Status | Verification Mechanism / Proof |
|---|---|---|---|
| **1. Feature Generation Timing** | Does `fv.ts` look ahead? | `RULED OUT` | [buffers.rs](file:///C:/Bot%20mk3/crates/bot-data/src/features_v2/buffers.rs) ring arrays only push at exact `T0`. `FeatureEngineV2::maybe_emit()` emits based on discrete window boundaries strictly `<` current ingestion time. |
| **2. Order Book Timing** | Does edge calculation peek at future mid-price? | `RULED OUT` | [agent.rs](file:///C:/Bot%20mk3/crates/bot-server/src/services/orchestrator/agent.rs) extracts mid explicitly *before* calculating expected costs. Simulator checks intent prices strictly against current BBO levels. |
| **3. Trade/Tape Aggregation** | Do 5s/1m flow windows leak future trades? | `RULED OUT` | Aggregation logic processes arrays chronologically. `sum_qty` uses reverse traversal (`idx = 0` is current), dropping trades with `ts > now()`. |
| **4. External Events (OI / Funding)**| Are delayed API endpoints applied retroactively?| `MITIGATED` | OI/Funding arrives asynchronously. [FeatureEngineV2](file:///C:/Bot%20mk3/crates/bot-data/src/features_v2/mod.rs#105-132) correctly processes them with their exact [recv_time](file:///C:/Bot%20mk3/crates/bot-data/src/features_v2/mod.rs#652-686) relative lag without back-dating historic rows natively. |
| **5. Regime Calculation Timing** | Do MAs leak future values? | `RULED OUT` | Expected MAs explicitly evaluate up to `FeatureRow.ts`. No smoothing splines or forward-peeking functions are applied. |
| **6. Execution/Risk Timing** | Does [agent.rs](file:///C:/Bot%20mk3/crates/bot-server/src/services/orchestrator/agent.rs) use `T+1` features during eval? | `RULED OUT` | `SymbolAgent::handle_action` relies exclusively on `self.last_features` populated strictly by the chronologically exact `emit_result` from [FeatureEngine](file:///C:/Bot%20mk3/crates/bot-data/src/features_v2/mod.rs#105-132). |
| **7. Action/Label Alignment** | Did the loaded ML model cheat using `T+n` targets?| `OPEN RISK` | Training logic occurs purely offline in Python. **Corrective Action**: Must verify that the offline Feature DataFrame indices align securely. |
| **8. Simulator Fill Alignment** | Does `EntryMode::Maker` fill immediately at intent?| `OPEN RISK` | Basic backtest logic natively assumes fill at touch. **Corrective Action**: Require integration of a queue-position or probability-decay fill model in Simulator. |
| **9. Event vs Recv Time Lag** | Do local network delays cause stream desync? | `MITIGATED` | `agent.rs/desync_watchdog` explicitly aborts trading via `degraded_timeout` and limits latency gaps to `1000ms`. |
| **10. Buffer Indexing Lookahead** | Does `buffer[0]` equal `T+1`?| `RULED OUT` | `RingBuffer::push()` enforces `buffer[0]` is the *most recently arrived* update. All windowed iterations scan backwards into history `[0..N]`. |

## Corrective Action Plan for Open Risks

1. **Simulator Fill Alignment (Risk 8)**: Update [bot-server/src/services/backtest.rs](file:///C:/Bot%20mk3/crates/bot-server/src/services/backtest.rs) to delay `EntryMode::Maker` fills probabilistically, enforcing at least 1-tick delay or volume-ahead queue checks natively.
2. **Action/Label Alignment (Risk 7)**: Ensure `Target_Move_Bps` is purely derived from `shift(-N)` logically in offline modeling. Not explicitly addressable in Rust runtime, but documented as an operational requirement.

**Audit Status:** Baseline temporal integrity is strong across the Rust runtime natively. Open Execution Simulator risks will be addressed before proceeding to walk-forward validations.
